Part 3: Base OS ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶Ü‡¶™
3.1 ‡¶∏‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá‡¶Æ ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶°‡ßá‡¶ü
bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt full-upgrade -y
sudo apt autoremove -y
sudo apt clean
3.2 Locale ‡¶ì Timezone
bash
# Timezone ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü
sudo timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Dhaka

# Locale ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü
sudo sed -i 's/^# en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8/en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8/' /etc/locale.gen
sudo locale-gen en_US.UTF-8
sudo update-locale en_US.UTF-8

# NTP enable
sudo timedatectl set-ntp true
3.3 Hostname ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü
bash
sudo hostnamectl set-hostname pi3b-server
echo "127.0.0.1    pi3b-server" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts
3.4 SSH hardening
bash
# SSH config ‡¶è‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü
sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config

# ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶®‡¶ó‡ßÅ‡¶≤‡ßã ‡¶Ü‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:
# Port 2222 (optional, security ‡¶ú‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø)
# PermitRootLogin no
# PasswordAuthentication no (key-based login ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶ú‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø)

sudo systemctl restart ssh
3.5 Swapfile ‡¶Ö‡¶™‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶ú‡ßá‡¶∂‡¶® (Raspberry Pi 3B memory ‡¶ï‡¶Æ)
bash
# ‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶´‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü swap ‡¶¨‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ß ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®
sudo dphys-swapfile swapoff
sudo systemctl disable dphys-swapfile
sudo apt purge dphys-swapfile -y

# ZRAM ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶Ü‡¶™ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶® (recommended for Pi 3B)
sudo apt install zram-tools -y
sudo nano /etc/default/zramswap
‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡¶®‡¶´‡¶ø‡¶ó‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶∂‡¶® ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:

text
ALGO=zstd
PERCENT=100
PRIORITY=100
bash
sudo systemctl enable zramswap
sudo systemctl start zramswap
Part 4: Docker ‡¶á‡¶®‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶∂‡¶® (64-bit)
4.1 Docker ‡¶á‡¶®‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶≤
bash
# Docker ‡¶è‡¶∞ dependencies ‡¶á‡¶®‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶≤
sudo apt install -y \
    ca-certificates \
    curl \
    gnupg \
    lsb-release

# Docker GPG key ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/debian/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg

# Repository ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó
echo \
  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/debian \
  $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

# Docker ‡¶á‡¶®‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶≤
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-compose-plugin

# Docker service enable
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
4.2 User permission
bash
# pi user ‡¶ï‡ßá docker group ‡¶è ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó
sudo usermod -aG docker pi

# ‡¶®‡¶§‡ßÅ‡¶® group permission apply ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶§‡ßá logout/login ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®
# ‡¶Ö‡¶•‡¶¨‡¶æ
newgrp docker
4.3 Docker configuration
bash
# Docker daemon configuration
sudo nano /etc/docker/daemon.json
‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ configuration ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:

json
{
  "log-driver": "json-file",
  "log-opts": {
    "max-size": "10m",
    "max-file": "3"
  },
  "storage-driver": "overlay2",
  "default-ulimits": {
    "nofile": {
      "Name": "nofile",
      "Hard": 65535,
      "Soft": 65535
    }
  }
}
bash
sudo systemctl restart docker
Part 5: Pi-hole (Docker-‡¶è)
5.1 Docker network ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø
bash
# Bridge network ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø
docker network create pihole_network
5.2 Pi-hole container ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶®
bash
# Directory ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø
mkdir -p ~/docker/pihole
cd ~/docker/pihole

# docker-compose.yml ‡¶´‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤ ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø
nano docker-compose.yml
‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ content ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:

yaml
version: "3.8"

services:
  pihole:
    container_name: pihole
    image: pihole/pihole:latest
    platform: linux/arm64
    ports:
      - "53:53/tcp"
      - "53:53/udp"
      - "80:80/tcp"
      - "443:443/tcp"
    environment:
      TZ: 'Asia/Dhaka'
      WEBPASSWORD: '‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞_‡¶∂‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶∂‡¶æ‡¶≤‡ßÄ_‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶∏‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶°'
      DNS1: '1.1.1.1'
      DNS2: '8.8.8.8'
      REV_SERVER: 'false'
    volumes:
      - './etc-pihole:/etc/pihole'
      - './etc-dnsmasq.d:/etc/dnsmasq.d'
    networks:
      - pihole_network
    restart: unless-stopped
    healthcheck:
      test: ['CMD', 'curl', '-f', 'http://localhost/admin/']
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3

networks:
  pihole_network:
    external: true
5.3 Pi-hole ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶≤‡ßÅ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®
bash
# Container ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶≤‡ßÅ
docker compose up -d

# Logs ‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶ï
