7.2 Device ‡¶™‡ßá‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Ç
bash
# Registration
sudo earnapp register
‡¶è‡¶á ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßç‡¶° ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø URL ‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶¶‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶∂‡¶® ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ô‡ßç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ó‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßá:

EarnApp ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá ‡¶≤‡¶ó‡¶á‡¶® ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®

‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡ßá‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶®‡ßç‡¶® ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®

"Device is successfully paired" ‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ú ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶æ ‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá

7.3 systemd service ‡¶ï‡¶®‡¶´‡¶ø‡¶ó‡¶æ‡¶∞
bash
# Service ‡¶´‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤ ‡¶è‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/earnapp.service
‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ content ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:

ini
[Unit]
Description=EarnApp Node
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
ExecStart=/usr/bin/earnapp run
Restart=always
RestartSec=10
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal

# Resource limits (Pi 3B optimization)
MemoryMax=200M
CPUQuota=50%

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
7.4 Service enable ‡¶è‡¶¨‡¶Ç ‡¶∂‡ßÅ‡¶∞‡ßÅ
bash
# systemd reload
sudo systemctl daemon-reload

# Service enable
sudo systemctl enable earnapp

# Service start
sudo systemctl start earnapp

# Status check
sudo systemctl status earnapp

# Logs ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡ßÅ‡¶®
sudo journalctl -u earnapp -f
Part 8: ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ü‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶ì ‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶á‡¶®‡¶ü‡ßá‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßç‡¶∏
8.1 ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶™‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶§‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ü‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Ç
bash
# Temperature monitoring script ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø
sudo nano /usr/local/bin/check-temp
‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá‡¶∞ content ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶®:

bash
#!/bin/bash
CPU_TEMP=$(vcgencmd measure_temp | cut -d= -f2 | cut -d\' -f1)
CPU_CLOCK=$(vcgencmd measure_clock arm | awk -F= '{print $2/1000000" MHz"}')
CPU_USAGE=$(top -bn1 | grep "Cpu(s)" | awk '{print $2}')

echo "CPU Temperature: $CPU_TEMP¬∞C"
echo "CPU Frequency: $CPU_CLOCK"
echo "CPU Usage: $CPU_USAGE%"

# Alert if temperature > 75¬∞C
if (( $(echo "$CPU_TEMP > 75" | bc -l) )); then
    echo "WARNING: High temperature detected!"
fi
bash
# Executable permission ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶®
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/check-temp

# Crontab ‡¶è ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶® (‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶§‡¶ø 5 ‡¶Æ‡¶ø‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ü‡ßá)
(crontab -l 2>/dev/null; echo "*/5 * * * * /usr/local/bin/check-temp >> /var/log/temp-check.log") | crontab -
